  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Public-Private Partnerships: Facilitating Legal Pathways for the International Labour Force in Turkey</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This proposed project focuses on addressing the drivers of irregular migration by facilitating the regularization of labour in Turkey. More specifically, the action will support the Directorate General on International Labour Force (DGIL) in its efforts to increase economic opportunities and create job opportunities in Turkey, support job growth and provide alternatives to irregular migration. It is centred on the idea of providing durable solutions that include access to employment for refugees and migrants to promote local labour market integration.</narrative>
  </description>
